Detailed Description

cvmx_usbc::_diepmsk

Device IN Endpoint Common Interrupt Mask Register (DIEPMSK)

This register works with each of the Device IN Endpoint Interrupt (DIEPINTn) registers for all endpoints to generate an interrupt per IN endpoint. The IN endpoint interrupt for a specific status in the DIEPINTn register can be masked by writing to the corresponding bit in this register. Status bits are masked by default. Mask interrupt: 1'b0 Unmask interrupt: 1'b1
